What is certainly pleasant here is the walking area along the quays, which in itself is a lot of fun.  The images are certainly worth taking a moment to admire, but you have to follow the paths between the trees to see them all. They sometimes seem to be somewhat hidden in the park.  The collection is rather limited and does not seem to me to be alive, with little new or recent work.  This makes the function more of a recreational park for walkers and cyclists.
